WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.090 --> 00:00:03.510
When I was 16, I was
focusing on becoming

00:00:03.510 --> 00:00:05.340
a good open source developer.

00:00:05.340 --> 00:00:07.590
I love the fact that I'm
still working on something

00:00:07.590 --> 00:00:09.750
I was passionate about as a teenager,

00:00:09.750 --> 00:00:12.024
and I think this is
gonna be my life mission.

00:00:12.024 --> 00:00:14.524
(calm music)

00:00:15.720 --> 00:00:18.810
Replit is the place where
you go with an idea in mind,

00:00:18.810 --> 00:00:20.700
no coding skills whatsoever,

00:00:20.700 --> 00:00:23.370
expressing in natural language
what you want to build,

00:00:23.370 --> 00:00:26.070
and then they see the
magic for the first time.

00:00:26.070 --> 00:00:29.460
We made coding so accessible to everyone.

00:00:29.460 --> 00:00:31.590
They don't even feel that
they're writing code anymore.

00:00:31.590 --> 00:00:34.050
They're just creating an
idea they have in their mind

00:00:34.050 --> 00:00:35.880
and turning it into one application,

00:00:35.880 --> 00:00:37.350
turning it into a website.

00:00:37.350 --> 00:00:39.960
- So when you started
building the Replit agent

00:00:39.960 --> 00:00:42.150
and you were experimenting
with different models,

00:00:42.150 --> 00:00:44.490
why did you land on using Claude?

00:00:44.490 --> 00:00:48.180
- We need high IQ level in our agent.

00:00:48.180 --> 00:00:49.440
I love to use this analogy

00:00:49.440 --> 00:00:51.420
where models are like the car engine

00:00:51.420 --> 00:00:54.870
and we're building the entire
car around it ourselves.

00:00:54.870 --> 00:00:58.320
In order for us to remove the
barrier of entry of coding,

00:00:58.320 --> 00:01:01.350
the power of the model is
what makes the difference.

00:01:01.350 --> 00:01:04.290
We made a choice back in early 2024,

00:01:04.290 --> 00:01:06.960
where Sonnet 3.5 came out,

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:09.840
and since then, Anthropic
kept the lead in having

00:01:09.840 --> 00:01:12.090
the best coding models on the market.

00:01:12.090 --> 00:01:14.340
- So one of my favorite parts of my job

00:01:14.340 --> 00:01:16.860
in applied AI is when we work with you

00:01:16.860 --> 00:01:19.890
on early research previews
of our newest models.

00:01:19.890 --> 00:01:23.719
- It feels like receiving
a shiny toy at Christmas.

00:01:23.719 --> 00:01:24.690
(both laughing)

00:01:24.690 --> 00:01:26.820
The discovery process of finding out

00:01:26.820 --> 00:01:30.303
what it's capable to do is the
most exciting window of time.

00:01:31.470 --> 00:01:35.520
Early 2025, you gave us
access to Sonnet 3.7.

00:01:35.520 --> 00:01:38.310
We rushed to create Replit Agent V2,

00:01:38.310 --> 00:01:41.040
and the moment Anthropic
launched the new model

00:01:41.040 --> 00:01:42.690
and we launched it in the same day,

00:01:42.690 --> 00:01:46.710
our new agent, there was a
incredible marketing pop.

00:01:46.710 --> 00:01:47.910
- And this is something that's used

00:01:47.910 --> 00:01:49.770
by relatively few people at the moment?

00:01:49.770 --> 00:01:52.500
It's kind of a hidden secret or?

00:01:52.500 --> 00:01:55.380
- I think we recently crossed
40 million registered users.

00:01:55.380 --> 00:01:58.350
We got a lot of attention
because users experienced

00:01:58.350 --> 00:02:01.920
something that they've never
seen before in our product.

00:02:01.920 --> 00:02:04.110
- [Hannah] So what makes Replit unique?

00:02:04.110 --> 00:02:06.030
- We remove all the complexity

00:02:06.030 --> 00:02:09.090
that makes the job of a
software engineer really hard.

00:02:09.090 --> 00:02:11.730
That barrier has been
completely crushed by Replit.

00:02:11.730 --> 00:02:14.730
I'm approached by people
that didn't even feel

00:02:14.730 --> 00:02:17.130
the permission to create
software in their life.

00:02:17.130 --> 00:02:19.290
They always had like an
amazing business idea.

00:02:19.290 --> 00:02:22.293
Now, they're doing the zero
to one complete in Replit.

00:02:23.503 --> 00:02:25.702
This is changing people's lives.

00:02:25.702 --> 00:02:28.369
(upbeat music)

